p:
Shading is a likely management technique for adapting coffee to warmer climates (
 Lin, 2007; 
 Pinto et al., 2008). Previous studies suggested that shade trees protect crops from high temperatures (
 Barradas and Fanjul 1986; 
 Morais et al., 2006; 
 Lin, 2007), frosts (
 Caramori et al., 1986), strong winds (
 Pezzopane et al., 2011) and, in extended dry periods, increase soil moisture and air humidity (
 Beer et al., 1998). The benefits reduce coffee physiological stress, adapting the plants to high climate variability.
